{
  "answer": "**In the *Manusmṛti* (Chapter 3), the eight named forms of marriage—*Brāhma*, *Daiva*, *Ārṣa*, *Prājāpatya*, *Āsura*, *Gāndharva*, *Rākṣasa*, and *Paiśāca*—are enumerated together in verses 20–21.[^1]**\n\n> Now learn in summary these eight forms of marriage for women, for the four *varnas*, which are beneficial and harmful in this world and the next. The `Brāhma`, the `Daiva`, and also the `Ārṣa`; the `Prājāpatya` and the `Āsura`; the `Gāndharva` and the `Rākṣasa`; and the eighth and lowest, the `Paiśāca`.[^1]\n\nThese match the details given: the *Gāndharva* is \"the voluntary union of a maiden and her lover...which springs from desire\" (verse 32);[^2] the *Rākṣasa* involves \"the forcible abduction of a maiden...after her kinsmen have been slain\" (verse 33);[^3] and the *Paiśāca* is \"when a man secretly approaches a girl who is sleeping [or] intoxicated...the eighth and most wicked\" (verse 34).[^4]\n\n[^1]: *Manusmṛti* (unknown-manusmrti-347b76), Chapter 3, [paragraphs p-36d967 to p-b07c61](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/03/translation/#p-36d967).\n[^2]: *Manusmṛti* (unknown-manusmrti-347b76), Chapter 3, [p-beb0f2](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/03/translation/#p-beb0f2).\n[^3]: *Manusmṛti* (unknown-manusmrti-347b76), Chapter 3, [p-2f28cf](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/03/translation/#p-2f28cf).\n[^4]: *Manusmṛti* (unknown-manusmrti-347b76), Chapter 3, [p-ca03b2](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/03/translation/#p-ca03b2).",
